{"title_page": "2020 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season", "text_new": "{{short description|45th season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = Tampa Bay Buccaneers\n| logo            = Tampa Bay Buccaneers wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          = \n| division_place  = \n| coach           = [[Bruce Arians]]\n| owner           = [[Malcolm Glazer|The Glazer family]]\n| general manager = [[Jason Licht]]\n| stadium         = [[Raymond James Stadium]]\n| playoffs        = \n| pro bowlers.    = \n| uniform         = [[File:Tampabay buccaneers unif20.png|200px]]\n| shortnavlink    = Buccaneers seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]' upcoming 45th in the [[National Football League]] and their second under [[List of Tampa Bay Buccaneers head coaches|head coach]] [[Bruce Arians]]. They will attempt to improve upon their 7\u20139 record from the [[2019 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|previous season]] and make the playoffs for the first time since [[2007 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|2007]]. They will also attempt to become the first team to play in the Super Bowl on their home field.\n\nFor the first time since [[2014 NFL season|2014]], quarterback [[Jameis Winston]] will not be on the Buccaneers' roster. On March 20, 2020, the team agreed to terms with former [[New England Patriots]] quarterback [[Tom Brady]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.buccaneers.com/news/tom-brady-qb-buccaneers-free-agency-roster-move |title=ALL IN! TOM BRADY, BUCS TEAM UP TO PURSUE CHAMPIONSHIPS |last=Smith |first=Scott |date=March 21, 2020 |website=Buccaneers.com |access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref> The Buccaneers also traded for Brady's former Patriots teammate, tight end [[Rob Gronkowski]].\n\nAlso, the team received new uniforms that were unveiled on April 7, 2020, for the first time since 2014. The new uniforms are similar in design to the ones they donned from 1997 to 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.buccaneers.com/news/bucs-to-get-new-uniforms-2020-season |title=Buccaneers to Introduce New Uniforms in 2020 |last=Smith |first=Scott |date=February 27, 2020 |website=Buccaneers.com |language=en-US |access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Roster changes ==\n\n=== Free agency ===\nThe Buccaneers entered free agency with the following:<ref>{{cite web|title=Buccaneers UFA|url=http://www.spotrac.com/nfl/free-agents/all/tampa-bay-buccaneers/|work=Spotrac|accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Unrestricted ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Position\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Player\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers|year=2020|border=2}}\" |2020 team\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Date signed\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Contract\n|-\n|[[Linebacker|OLB]]\n|[[Sam Acho]]\n|\n|\n|\n|-style=\"background:#cfc\"\n|[[Safety (gridiron football position)|FS]]\n|[[Andrew Adams (American football)|Andrew Adams]]\n|Tampa Bay Buccaneers\n|March 22, 2020<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/gregauman/status/1241767518118858754|title=Bucs safety Andrew Adams' new contract to return for 2020 is one year, $1.01-million. Qualifies for minimum salary benefit -- minimum for his experience is $910,000, and with MSB would only count $750,000 for cap purposes.|last=Auman|first=Greg|date=2020-03-22|website=twitter.com|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|1 year, $1.01M<ref name=\":13\" />\n|-style=\"background:#fcc\"\n|[[Defensive tackle|DT]]\n|[[Beau Allen]]\n|[[2020 New England Patriots season|New England Patriots]]\n|March 18, 2020<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/caplannfl/status/1240394668468207617|title=#Patriots are signing former #Buccaneers DT Beau Allen: deal is for 2 years, $8m max total, source said.|last=Caplan|first=Adam|