{"title_page": "Trevor Nkosi", "text_new": "{{AFC submission|||ts=20200425165718|u=ZS Khumalo|ns=0}}\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[The Honourable]]\n| name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| honorific-suffix = [[Councillor]]\n| office = [[Whip]] of Council at the [[Gert Sibande District Municipality]] \n| deputy = \n| term_start =  August 2016\n| term_end =\n| office1 = Gert Sibande ANCYL regional secretary\n| term_start1    =  2013\n| term_end1  =   2015 \n| predecessor1 = Zakes Masilela \n|successor1   = James Nkosi\n| office2 = Deputy chairperson of the Mpumalanga ANCYL\n| term_start2 = June 2016\n| prior_term1 = \n| birthname = Trevor Gladson Siboniso Nkosi\n| birth_date = 27 April 1983\n| birth_place = [[Ermelo]], Mpumalanga\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| citizenship = South Africa\n| nationality = [[South Africa]]n\n| party = [[African National Congress]] \n| spouse = \n| relations = \n| children = \n| education = Cebisa High School\n| profession = Politician\n| residence = [[Ermelo]]\n| parents =  Madoda Ephraim Nkosi, Thoko Elizabeth Nkosi\n}}\n\n'''Trevor Siboniso Nkosi''' (born 27 April 1983 in [[Ermelo]]) is a [[Whip]] of [[Council]] at the [[Gert Sibande District Municipality]], [[Mpumalanga]] in [[South Africa]]<ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/61887/gsdm-chief-whip-gives-motivation-to-cebisas-grade-12-learners/ GSDM chief whip gives motivation to Cebisa's Grade 12 learners], Highvelder, 13 April 2018. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/70306/gsdm-chief-whip-hosts-info-session-for-the-elderly/ GSDM chief whip hosts info session for the elderly], Highvelder, 26 October 2018. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/54058/chief-whip-lends-helping-hand-chrissiesmeer/ Chief whip lends helping hand in Chrissiesmeer], 14 September 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. He is also a former elected regional secretary of the [[African National Congress Youth League|ANC Youth League]] in the [[Gert Sibande]] region as well as its regional chairperson<ref>[https://ridgetimes.co.za/162165/municipal-officials-suspended/ Municipal officials suspended], Ridge Times, 22 May 2014. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://ridgetimes.co.za/163995/politicians-clear-air/ Politicians clear the air], Ridge Times, 11 February 2015. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://013.co.za/2017/05/04/ancyl-says-trevor-nkosi-bodyguards-personal-thing/ ANCYL says Trevor Nkosi bodyguards a 'personal thing'], 013News, 4 May 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://013.co.za/2017/08/01/gert-sibande-branches-choose-trevors-successor/ Gert Sibande branches to choose Trevor's successor], 013News, 1 August 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. In June 2016, Nkosi was elected to the position of leading the league the whole of Mpumalanga as its provincial deputy chairperson<ref>[https://www.dailysun.co.za/News/National/education-comes-first-for-leaders-20160721 Education comes first for leaders], [[Daily Sun]], 21 July 2016. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[http://highvelder.co.za/37788/ancyls-hand-remains-open ANCYL's hand remains open], Highvelder, 22 July 2016. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. He had also served as Youth Co-ordinator for the Gert Sibande District Municipality<ref>[http://highvelder.co.za/167003/youth-office-hosts-dialogue Youth office hosts dialogue], 20 November 2015. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://municipalities.co.za/management/132/gert-sibande-district-municipality Gert Sibande District Municipality Council & Management]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nkosi, Trevor}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century South African politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[The Honourable]]\n| name = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| honorific-suffix = [[Councillor]]\n| office = [[Whip]] of Council at the [[Gert Sibande District Municipality]] \n| deputy = \n| term_start =  August 2016\n| term_end =\n| office1 = Gert Sibande ANCYL regional secretary\n| term_start1    =  2013\n| term_end1  =   2015 \n| predecessor1 = Zakes Masilela \n|successor1   = James Nkosi\n| office2 = Deputy chairperson of the Mpumalanga ANCYL\n| term_start2 = June 2016\n| prior_term1 = \n| birthname = Trevor Gladson Siboniso Nkosi\n| birth_date = 27 April 1983\n| birth_place = [[Ermelo]], Mpumalanga\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| citizenship = South Africa\n| nationality = [[South Africa]]n\n| party = [[African National Congress]] \n| spouse = \n| relations = \n| children = \n| education = Cebisa High School\n| profession = Politician\n| residence = [[Ermelo]]\n| parents =  Madoda Ephraim Nkosi, Thoko Elizabeth Nkosi\n}}\n\n'''Trevor Siboniso Nkosi''' (born 27 April 1983 in [[Ermelo]]) is a [[Whip]] of [[Council]] at the [[Gert Sibande District Municipality]], [[Mpumalanga]] in [[South Africa]]<ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/61887/gsdm-chief-whip-gives-motivation-to-cebisas-grade-12-learners/ GSDM chief whip gives motivation to Cebisa's Grade 12 learners], Highvelder, 13 April 2018. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/70306/gsdm-chief-whip-hosts-info-session-for-the-elderly/ GSDM chief whip hosts info session for the elderly], Highvelder, 26 October 2018. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://highvelder.co.za/54058/chief-whip-lends-helping-hand-chrissiesmeer/ Chief whip lends helping hand in Chrissiesmeer], 14 September 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. He is also a former elected regional secretary of the [[African National Congress Youth League|ANC Youth League]] in the [[Gert Sibande]] region as well as its regional chairperson<ref>[https://ridgetimes.co.za/162165/municipal-officials-suspended/ Municipal officials suspended], Ridge Times, 22 May 2014. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://ridgetimes.co.za/163995/politicians-clear-air/ Politicians clear the air], Ridge Times, 11 February 2015. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://013.co.za/2017/05/04/ancyl-says-trevor-nkosi-bodyguards-personal-thing/ ANCYL says Trevor Nkosi bodyguards a 'personal thing'], 013News, 4 May 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[https://013.co.za/2017/08/01/gert-sibande-branches-choose-trevors-successor/ Gert Sibande branches to choose Trevor's successor], 013News, 1 August 2017. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. In June 2016, Nkosi was elected to the position of leading the league the whole of Mpumalanga as its provincial deputy chairperson<ref>[https://www.dailysun.co.za/News/National/education-comes-first-for-leaders-20160721 Education comes first for leaders], [[Daily Sun]], 21 July 2016. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref> <ref>[http://highvelder.co.za/37788/ancyls-hand-remains-open ANCYL's hand remains open], Highvelder, 22 July 2016. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>. He had also served as Youth Co-ordinator for the Gert Sibande District Municipality<ref>[http://highvelder.co.za/167003/youth-office-hosts-dialogue Youth office hosts dialogue], 20 November 2015. Retrieved 25 April 2020</ref>.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://municipalities.co.za/management/132/gert-sibande-district-municipality Gert Sibande District Municipality Council & Management]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nkosi, Trevor}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century South African politicians]]\n", "name_user": "ZS Khumalo", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trevor_Nkosi"}
